👨‍⚕️ Hi, I'm Dr James O'Donovan. I hold a medical degree (MBBS), Masters Degree (MRes) in Ageing and Health, and PhD (DPhil) in Digital Education. 

📚 My goal is to make health topics easy to understand and accessible!

⏰ Long form content WEEKLY - WEDNESDAY AND SUNDAYS & Shorts daily!

 Please SUBSCRIBE & join our community of likeminded learners. 

⚠️ Disclaimer: Information on this channel is intended as a free open-access EDUCATIONAL resource and not as clinical advice. Doctor O'Donovan Medical Education Ltd. can not provide individual medical advice. All information is accurate to the best of my knowledge at the time of publication. Medical education videos on Doctor O'Donovan Medical Education Ltd. are not a substitute for professional professional medical advice, diagnosis or treatment. NEVER ignore professional medical advice because of something you have heard here. ALWAYS consult your doctor regarding any concerns about your condition or treatment.

UK GMC Number: 7436647

description.simpleText:
In this video Doctor O'Donovan explains the Brain Natriuretic Peptide (BNP or NT-proBNP)) blood test including 1. What BNP is 2. Why it's used 3. How to interpret the test 4. What affects the result. 

BNP is a blood test used to detect Heart Failure. 

Remember to like the video, leave a comment and subscribe to the channel for weekly videos. 

Further information: https://cks.nice.org.uk/topics/heart-failure-chronic/diagnosis/how-to-assess/
************************************************************************

YouTube: www.youtube.com/doctorodonovan​
Instagram: @doctorodonovan
Twitter: @doctorodonovan
